<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <%- include("partial/header.ejs") %>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/faq.css" />
  </head>

  <body>
    <%- include("partial/nav.ejs") %>
    <main id="faq">
      <div class="container-faq">
        <h1>NIT Warangal Clubs and Societies FAQs</h1>

        <h2>General Questions</h2>
        <div class="faq">
          <div class="question">
            1. What are clubs and societies at NIT Warangal?
          </div>
          <div class="answer">
            Clubs and societies at NIT Warangal are student-run organizations
            that cater to a wide range of interests, hobbies, and academic
            pursuits.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq">
          <div class="question">
            2. How many clubs and societies are there at NIT Warangal?
          </div>
          <div class="answer">
            NIT Warangal boasts a diverse array of clubs and societies, with
            over 50 active organizations covering various fields such as
            technology, arts, culture, sports, literature, and community
            service.
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- More questions and answers -->

        <h2>Membership and Joining</h2>
        <div class="faq">
          <div class="question">3. Can anyone join a club or society?</div>
          <div class="answer">
            Yes, absolutely! All students of NIT Warangal are encouraged to join
            clubs and societies that align with their interests and goals.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq">
          <div class="question">4. How can I join a club or society?</div>
          <div class="answer">
            Joining a club or society is simple. Each club typically holds
            membership drives or orientations at the beginning of the academic
            year, where interested students can sign up and learn more about the
            club's activities.
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- More questions and answers -->

        <h2>Leadership and Activities</h2>
        <div class="faq">
          <div class="question">
            5. Are there any leadership opportunities within clubs and
            societies?
          </div>
          <div class="answer">
            Yes, clubs and societies offer various leadership opportunities for
            students who are interested in taking on roles such as president,
            vice president, treasurer, secretary, or event coordinator.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq">
          <div class="question">
            6. How can I contribute to a club or society if I'm unable to attend
            regular meetings?
          </div>
          <div class="answer">
            If you're unable to attend regular meetings due to academic or
            personal commitments, there are still plenty of ways to contribute
            to a club or society.
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- More questions and answers -->

        <h2>Community Engagement</h2>
        <div class="faq">
          <div class="question">
            7. Are there any community service opportunities through clubs and
            societies?
          </div>
          <div class="answer">
            Yes, many clubs and societies actively engage in community service
            initiatives, such as volunteering at local schools, organizing
            charity drives, or participating in environmental clean-up projects.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq">
          <div class="question">
            8. Can alumni get involved with clubs and societies?
          </div>
          <div class="answer">
            Absolutely! Alumni are welcome to stay connected with their alma
            mater by getting involved with clubs and societies as mentors, guest
            speakers, or advisors.
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- More questions and answers -->
      </div>
    </main>

    <%- include("partial/footer.ejs") %>

    <script>
      // JavaScript to toggle answer visibility
      const questions = document.querySelectorAll(".question");
      questions.forEach((question) => {
        question.addEventListener("click", () => {
          const answer = question.nextElementSibling;
          answer.style.display =
            answer.style.display === "block" ? "none" : "block";
        });
      });
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
